<TITLE> BNP opposes power price hike plan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 14 (bdnews24.com) Main opposition BNP on Friday expressed its reservations about the government's plan to hike power price. The party's standing committee member Nazrul Islam Khan termed the decision 'irrational' at a briefing at Dhaka metropolitan BNP's Naya Paltan office. He added that BNP cannot appreciate the price hike as the government has failed to supply adequate power. The senior BNP leader metaphorically described the move as putting more burden on a struggling man. On Wednesday, Tawfik-e-Elahi Chowdhury, the prime minister's power and energy adviser, said at a press briefing that electricity price might be hiked within two month
